### Pillar 7 — Interoceptive Precision: The Embodied Intelligence Upgrade *(New in Version 5.0)*
**IISL variable: B — interoceptive integration depth, and C — coherence via body-brain unity**

This pillar has no precedent in prior versions of this framework and represents one of Version 5.0's most significant theoretical contributions.

Intelligence in biological systems is not a function of the brain alone. It is a function of the brain-body system. The insular cortex — particularly the anterior insula — serves as the primary cortical hub for interoception: the real-time sensing of the body's internal state, including heart rate, gut activity, respiratory rhythm, immune signaling, and hormonal fluctuation. This interoceptive signal is not background noise. It is a primary input channel that shapes every high-level cognitive and emotional computation the brain performs.

Recent work has demonstrated that interoceptive precision — the accuracy and bandwidth of the brain's representation of bodily states — correlates strongly with emotional intelligence, decision-making quality under uncertainty, and subjective sense of identity coherence. It is, in the language of the IISL, a B variable that also contributes to C: more accurate interoception produces both richer structural integration (B_interoceptive component) and higher Φ, because the body becomes a more precisely integrated component of the system's unified causal structure.

The epigenetic architecture of insular cortex interoceptive maps is incompletely characterized but appears to involve the same BDNF-Arc plasticity machinery targeted in Pillar 1, suggesting that Pillar 1 interventions may have partial Pillar 7 effects. The targeted research agenda for Pillar 7 is to characterize the specific epigenetic markers governing insular-vagal connectivity and to develop CRISPRa targets that specifically increase interoceptive bandwidth.

**Research target:** EWAS of high versus low interoceptive precision subjects (measured via heartbeat detection tasks and fMRI insular-vagal coherence); CRISPRa targeting of identified loci in adult insular cortex progenitors.

**Mechanism on IISL:** Increases B_interoceptive and C simultaneously — the only intervention in the framework with direct leverage on both primary variables. The body-brain system, treated as a unified computational architecture, achieves higher Φ than the brain treated in isolation.

