**Parameter 1 — Sustained Adult Neuroplasticity.** CRISPRa upregulation of BDNF, Arc, and PSD-95 maintains the learning window open throughout the adult lifespan. Measured by synaptic density imaging, novel task learning rate in bits per unit time, and PCI score maintenance above young-adult baseline through age 70.

**Parameter 2 — Expanded Sensorium.** UVS opsin reactivation extends perception into UV (300–400nm); synthetic NIR opsin extends into near-infrared (700–1400nm). Measured by electroretinogram response, behavioral discrimination tasks, and fMRI cortical mapping of novel perceptual representations.

**Parameter 3 — Radiation-Hardened Cellular Architecture.** Somatic integration of Dsup and TRID1 achieves greater than 60% reduction in radiation-induced double-strand breaks. Measured by comet assay, clonogenic survival, and long-term genomic stability at 50 population doublings.

