## XIV. RESPONSES TO ANTICIPATED REBUTTALS

**"Silicon will reach AGI before biological enhancement matures."**
This is the timing objection addressed in Section X. The IISL is a claim about long-run attractor states. Silicon may reach AGI first. The carbon-first framework's claim is that it will be the only architecture still scaling after silicon plateaus. These are compatible statements.

**"Neuromorphic silicon will close the Φ gap."**
The quantitative Φ gap persists at four to six orders of magnitude per watt even for the most advanced neuromorphic architectures. Theoretical analysis suggests two to three orders of magnitude remain irreducible given the architectural constraints of planar silicon substrates. The three-dimensional, metabolically embedded, interoceptively grounded architecture of biological tissue is not reproducible in silicon without incurring energy costs that exceed the efficiency of biology.

**"Why not both? Use reversible silicon augmentation."**
SPF occurs even with reversible offloading because metabolic down-regulation happens over weeks at the molecular level, not only at the moment of disconnection. The down-regulation is the problem, not the disconnection event. Testable via H6.

**"Dsup might cause cancer."**
Initial studies show no increased oncogenesis in human cells up to 50 population doublings post-integration. Long-term safety monitoring is incorporated as a primary endpoint in H3, not a secondary one. The framework does not claim Dsup is safe in humans. It claims the safety question is answerable and must be answered before any human application.

**"This is just transhumanism."**
No. Transhumanism seeks to transcend biological limits by abandoning the biological substrate. The carbon-first framework seeks to optimize biological limits by engineering within the biological substrate. The distinction is categorical. Homo Intellectus remains biologically human in every architectural sense: organic, embodied, metabolically embedded, interoceptively grounded, and morally continuous with the humans who preceded it.

**"You are just proposing eugenics with different vocabulary."**
No. Eugenics was coercive, population-level, heritable selection operating on existing variation. DIE is voluntary, individual-level, somatic (non-heritable) engineering targeting specific molecular mechanisms. The only commonality is the word "biological." Comparing them requires ignoring every meaningful distinction between selection and engineering, coercion and consent, heritable and somatic, and population and individual.

**"The IISL exponents are speculative."**
They are empirically grounded initial estimates, not proofs. The paper states this explicitly and repeatedly. The exponents will be refined against H1–H8 experimental data. A theory that states falsifiable quantitative predictions is more scientific than one that does not, even if the predictions later require revision.

